The paper proposes an unsupervised method for learning representations over graphs, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method involves training a cross-graph attention network, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing (cs.CV, cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a common tool in many subfields of computer science (cs.NE).
